%S A394971 1,1,1,0,1,0,2,0,37,0,687115,0
%N A394971 Number of species of order n that contain row-Hamiltonian Latin squares.
%C A394971 A Latin square is row-Hamiltonian if the permutation mapping row i to row j consists of a single cycle, for all distinct i,j. A species (also called main class or paratopism class) is an equivalence class of Latin squares under the natural action of S_n wreath S_3.
%C A394971 a(n) = 0 if n > 2 is even [Wanless].
%D A394971 J. Allsop and I.M. Wanless, Perfect 1-factorisations of K_{11,11}, Australasian J. Combinatorics 95 (2026), 114-130.
%e A394971 The Cayley table of any cyclic group of prime order is a row-Hamiltonian Latin square.
%Y A394971 Cf. A394970, A120489.
%K A394971 nonn,more,new
%O A394971 1,7
%A A394971 _Ian Wanless_, Apr 08 2026
